  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving multi-purpose cash assistance to vulnerable communities in Kamonia, Kazumba, and Kangana. This FAO project provides cash assistance to 39,600 people, including 16,000 women, 11,000 men, and over 12,000 children. This project is part of an $80 million CERF allocation to support cash programming in response to increasing food insecurity in 6 countries.</narrative>
